title: For Sale:  Pre 57 K frame Smith & Wesson .38 Special 6 inch barrel 5 screw.
postcontent:
This is a pre 57 Smith & Wesson .38 Special, Fish hook hammer and a perfect trigger.
It was carried back in the 50s and into the 60s so there is the typical holster marks.
 I have shot it and at 25 yards it is as expected, one ragged hole.
The grip panels are walnut with matching numbers.
 Again there is no model number, it is before model numbers and is only listed as a K frame Smith & Wesson from the serial number it is a 1948 or 49, it has the half moon front sight and the .240 serrated trigger(grooved).
 It is a "C" designation 5 digit serial number. 
 The finish isn't perfect but not gone in no way, typical holster wear on muzzle but that's it. 
 From what I've read on the Ohio hunting regs it's legal to hunt deer with in Ohio so that could be a plus for somebody.
 I've seen them go for between $550 and $650 on the net but I'll take $500.00 to get it a new home, I don't shoot it anymore, but someone should.

title: For Sale/Trade:  LNIB Saiga Russian Izhmash 7.62x39 Fully-Converted AK Rifle with EXTRAS  +  640 Rds Ammo + 4 Mags
postcontent:
RUSSIAN IZHMASH SAIGA 7.62x39 AK RIFLE
Round Count is UNDER 50
FULLY CONVERTED
Comes with all of the ORIGINAL PARTS PLUS LOTS OF EXTRAS; I am a gunsmith and have 12 years of experience in that position as well as working as an Armorer for a local PD.  
I purchased three of these rifles approximately 3 years ago from FIME Group in Las Vegas for the cost of $1000 per rifle. At that time these guns were just the base rifles. First, I stripped each rifle and used a file on each of the receivers and took off just a little bit of metal, here and there, which tightened the tolerances. Then I removed the gas tubes and built ones slightly smaller in diameter and slightly shorter. This allows for better bolt cycling even when using smaller and less powerful loads. Next I sent the barrels for each rifle to a local metal shop, who acid washed them and dipped them each 3 times to ensure proper Chrome coverage on the insides of the barrels. Then I removed the trigger mechanisms for each gun. I replaced the factory slap triggers with Vortex trigger kits. These trigger kits are two stage triggers. They have very little Play and ZERO slap.  I then added G&G Aluminum Quad Rail Forends and G&G Vertical Forend Grips with "Out - the - Bottom" Bipods. Then I replaced the factory pistol grips with Hogue composite flat dark earth grips.  On this Rifle only, I added a composite rear trunion and tube and a MagPul or UTG 6 position stock.  The plastic trunion and tube could easily be switched out for aluminum versions, but at the time, it was all I could find. I replaced the recoil spring with a homemade double looped version which is much smoother than the originals. I made some other modifications here and there but these are the main ones. As you can see, I converted this gun far beyond what many shops do. I sold one of the others, that had a little more into it, plus a Trijicon Reflex Scope, for $2700 last fall. I have, on several occasions,  with surplus ammo, shot sub-3 inch groups at 400 meters with my other rifle that is the same as this one, with the exception of a little bit better scope.  That is NOT something that most AKs can accomplish. Also, recoil is very light. I have also dumped the 30 round mag in less than 6 seconds without the use of a slide fire stock. This Rifle also has a side mount and removable rail assembly with a Bushnell 6-9x40 illuminated scope. Lastly, I'm including 4 Mags and a sealed spam can of FMJ ammo (640 rds)
This Rifle is REALLY NICE and WELL MAINTAINED. It has Fired LESS THAN 50 TOTAL Rounds in It's Life.
I Don't Want to Sell it, But need Cash for Medical Bills, So it Has to Go.  Please Email with Questions. Please Send Me Offers. CASH ONLY OR CASH PLUS TRADES.  PLEASE NO LOW BALL OFFERS. IM NOT A PAWN SHOP. I DON'T WANT YOUR PHONE OR YOUR TECH ITEMS. GUNS or CASH ONLY PLEASE.

title: For Sale:  Norinco SKS Bullpup Custom lots of ammo and magazines
postcontent:
This is a Norinco SKS (Chinese) rifle that shoots the 7.62x39 round. I originally purchased this rifle when it was put together on a different plastic stock. I purchased it for 400. I installed a bullpup stock that I bought just over 200 and added a buffer recoil pad (to reduce recoil). The barrel still has a lot of life left in it. Shoots very accurately and flawlessly.

The upgraded bullpup stock shortens the SKS about 5-6 inches from the previous length. I originally built this because I enjoy learning the different weapon platforms and I thought this would be a great shooter. Absolutely no surprises, this rifle shoots beautifully. The few times that I took it to the range, there is always a small audience behind me trying to figure out what I'm shooting. If you have friends or family that shoots, or you just want to show someone up that is different from what everyone else has, then this is the rifle for you. Or if you just like to have fun and blast away with inexpensive steel ammo, then this is also for you.

Replacement parts for the Norinco are cheap and are plentiful because of U.S. companies making compatible parts between all of the SKS platforms for all the different countries who manufacture it. The overall recoil is very manageable, if you wanted to take someone with a small frame to range they would have a blast without any concerns of injury.

I figured that whoever wants to buy it will have to pay for the transfer and background check fee. So I cut the price down from 800 to 700 to help cover the cost of those transaction fees at whichever local gun shop we commit our transaction.

What is in this packaged deal?

1 Norinco SKS with a custom bullpup stock

800 rounds of ammunition (40 rounds of PDX1 Defender, 40 rounds of winchester white box brass, and the rest of the ammo is Tulammo steel cased)

5 20 round magazines
3 30 round magazines
2 40 round magazines
(all magazines are reliable)

20 stripper clips (for quick ammo loading)

1 steel ammo can with 7.62 markings.

NOTE: Magazines will be disassembled and provided to purchaser as parts kits, exactly how the gun shops in Colorado sell the magazines. This rifle is 922r compliant the entire stock kit is made in USA as well as the magazines and buffer pad that I installed.

If you are interested, please text me at 951 741 5147 or email me at stealmywheels@yahoo.com

title: For Sale/Trade:  British .303 No4 Mk1 Lee Enfield Rifle (FTR)
postcontent:
Here's your chance to own a piece of history. Based on the serial number this rifle was made in early 1944 by ROF Maltby in Yorkshire, England. It then went back to the factory sometime between 1948-1950 for parts repair/replacement post-war. Hence the FTR on the receiver (Factory Thorough Repair). We know it had to be between 1948-1950 since it is still an all original No4 Mk1 instead of being upgraded to the No4 Mk1/2 or Mk1/3 which started in 1950 and continued through to 1954. That is about all the history I know about this particular rifle. As you can see in the pictures it has seen its fair share of use post FTR but is in good shape for its age. Clean barrel and still very good rifling.

It comes with one 10 round factory original magazine, two rounds, and a leather sling that is missing a snap button.

I'm looking to get $300 for everything. I'm also looking to trade for a Ruger American in .308 Winchester, Ruger LC9, Ruger SR22 with threaded barrel, Ruger LCR in .38 Special or .22LR, Crimson Trace LG-429M, Sig Sauer P226 in 9mm or .40S&W, or an AK-47/AKM with a chrome lined barrel.

1st Year Sino Soviet - Serial Number A5xxx

These are among the rarest rifles in the country. First year Chinese models produced on Russian equipment, under Russian supervision. Exported to Albania in the 1970's and sent "elsewhere."
